@"A request the provider's handler answers."
request ask() -> integer

@"Returns a `handler` as a FIRST-CLASS VALUE — a provider agent generic over the continuation's return type R. `handler[R, pure]` instantiates the provider's two implicit generics with make_handler's own R and a pure residual. This exercises the standalone-handler path (provider agent + closure), distinct from inline `use handler`."
agent make_handler[R]() -> (agent(...(agent() -> R with ask)) -> R) {
  return handler[R, pure] {
    request ask() { next 7 }
  }
}

@"Builds the provider value, then `use`s it: the rest of the block runs as the continuation under the provider's ask handler. ask() answers 7 each time, so 7 + 7 = 14."
agent main() -> integer {
  use make_handler[integer]()
  ask() + ask()
}
